The paper deals with the problem of secure communication over a Gaussian multiple access channel with an eavesdropper, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed coding scheme utilizes low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of random bit insertion and puncturing techniques, which are commonly used in communication systems (cs.MM) and network security (cs.NI).
